            "criterion_type": "diagnosis",
            "original_criterion_type": "diagnosis",
            "description": "Used to treat an indication listed in Table 1 (NCCN/FDA-supported cancers including: ampullary cancer, cervical cancer, CNS cancer, colorectal cancer [first-line and second-line metastatic, in combination with 5-FU], hepatocellular carcinoma [in combination with atezolizumab], kidney cancer/metastatic renal cell carcinoma [in combination with interferon-alfa], mesothelioma, non-small cell lung cancer [locally advanced, recurrent, or metastatic non-squamous, in combination with carboplatin and paclitaxel], ovarian cancer, fallopian tube cancer, primary peritoneal cancer [in combination with chemotherapy], small bowel adenocarcinoma, soft tissue sarcoma, uterine cancer, vaginal cancer, vulvar cancer, glioblastoma [disease that has progressed on prior therapy]) AND all indication-specific criteria are met",
            "logic_operator": "AND",
            "normalized_tokens": []
          },
          {
            "criterion_type": "other",
            "original_criterion_type": "other",
            "description": "The dose does not exceed either of the following: (a) 10 mg/kg every 2 weeks OR (b) 15 mg/kg every 3 weeks",
            "logic_operator": "AND",
            "normalized_tokens": []
          },
          {
            "criterion_type": "step_therapy",
            "original_criterion_type": "step_therapy",
            "description": "For Avastin, Alymsys, Avzivi, Jobevne, or Vegzelma requests only: the member has an inadequate response, contraindication, or intolerance to bevacizumab-awwb (Mvasi) OR bevacizumab-bvzr (Zirabev) \u2014 documentation must be submitted",
